dashboard_elements.body_text:
**Is Cached**: "No" sets the results to ignore cached queries, which have a significantly reduced runtime since the results were stored in memory. This means that we are looking at dashboard queries that _did_ run the query against the Database itself (be it base tables or Aggregate Aware tables). To include cached queries, set this filter to "Yes".

**Is Admin**: "No" will show the results for queries made by out _"regular"_ dashboard users. "Yes" will include results run by administrators which could be things like test queries or queries over long time ranges.

**Query Filters** can be used as a "contains" or "matches advanced" to filter out cases where dashboard users passed a specific filter to the dashboard. For example, if you set Query Filters to _matches (advanced)_ and entered: **%"7 days ago for 7 days"%** as the value, you would get results matching those that _definately_ use the Aggregate Tables in the Post-Optimization Tile, since our Aggregate tables currently filter on the "7 days ago for 7 days" time frame (our default time frame for embedded dashboards).
